glosses: To kick, to strike with the leg or foot.
To let someone down, to disappoint.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish تكمه اتمق or تكمه آتمق (tekme atmaḳ, “to give a kick”), from تكمه (tekme), deteriorated from تپمه (tepme) or دپمه (depme), equivalent to compound of tekme (“a kick”) + atmak (“to throw”), literally “to throw a kick”.
